Goals for determines who is ahead when two division rivals have the same record,i think.

Here, in order, is the tied-breaker criteria.  Although it's probably a little more relavent after 82 games.  lol  1) Wins: Most total wins among the tied teams. 2) Head-to-Head Record: Most points in games against each other among the tied teams. 3) Goal Differential: Using the total goals scored during the regular season, the greater positive differential between goals for and against among the tied teams.
